      "role": "user",
      "content": "coincidence?? i dont think so. i've been charting these movements for three weeks now. it's not just random. they form these specific triangles and circles whenever the humidity spikes. it's like they're using a code. i can literally feel the shift in the air when they start the pattern. it's more than just \"environmental cues,\" it's like they have a shared awareness of the atmospheric change before it even happens. don't you think there could be something more to it than just luck?",
