      "role": "user",
      "content": "but science only tracks what it's looking for, right? maybe they've been doing this for centuries and we just haven't developed the right framework to call it \"science\" yet. i'm not saying they're \"predicting\" it with magic, I'm saying they're communicating it. it feels so intentional. like, if i didn't spend all this time watching them, i'd just see \"random birds,\" but once you see the patterns, you can't unsee them. it's like a language. even if there's no \"official\" study on it, you can't tell me the math of their patterns doesn't line up with the pressure drops i'm seeing. isn't it possible we're just missing a whole layer of biological communication?",
